<div id="review_224755487" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/224755487" />
    <a title="Ron" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1256262-ron"><img alt="Ron" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442983573p2/1256262.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/224755487?book_show_action=true">Oct 18, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ron" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ron" href="/user/show/1256262-ron">Ron</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1256262-ron?shelf=ebook">ebook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1256262-ron?shelf=drama">drama</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1256262-ron?shelf=gutenberg">gutenberg</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer224755487" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9231155629365552039">Good, but not as good as I hoped/expected. While the Father Brown short stories are in one sense classic detective tales, they focus on the preternatural ability of the diminutive cleric to pull solutions out of (apparently) thin air. Since the reader is not given enough background to even make faulty conjectures, the fun is diminished.<br/><br/>The title character is a winning one, though I found myself substituting Alex Guinness&apos; image (who played the good father in an early movie adaptation) for that i</span>
  <span id="freeText9231155629365552039" style="display:none">Good, but not as good as I hoped/expected. While the Father Brown short stories are in one sense classic detective tales, they focus on the preternatural ability of the diminutive cleric to pull solutions out of (apparently) thin air. Since the reader is not given enough background to even make faulty conjectures, the fun is diminished.<br /><br />The title character is a winning one, though I found myself substituting Alex Guinness' image (who played the good father in an early movie adaptation) for that in the book.<br /><br />Not a cerebral as the Holmes stories, but much better hearted, as you'd expect. Brown is often more interested in saving the perpetrator's soul than bringing him/her to justice. He, after all, serves a higher court.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9231155629365552039" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


